Cisco Router Terminal
Basic start up configuration commands to perform when operating on a new router

![IOS-Configuration-Mangement](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/94019217/179380846-d19a7171-2f1e-4141-bba6-0998a4312d14.png)


- No initial configuration dialog
- Return!
#To enter privileged exec mode use the command enable or en.
- enable 
# en

#Enter the global configuration mode
- configure terminal 
# config t

#Change the hostname of the router to R1
- hostname R1

#Override command with “do” and check what interfaces are available on the router
- do show ip interface brief
# do sh ip int brief

#Configure an interface / assign an ip address
- Interface gigabitEthernet 0/0
- ip address {IP address} {net mask}
- no shutdown
- end

#View entire configuration starting from hostname
- show run | begin hostname
# sh run | begin hostname

#Copy the running configuration to the startup configuration
- Copy run start

#Backup the current running configuration to flash memory
- Copy run flash:

#Back up the current running configuration to an ftp server if possible
- Copy run ftp
- {ftp IP address}
- {destination filename}

#Reload device and ensure the correct configuration runs
- reload

